new standards for sustainable shellfish farming the leopold leadership program skip to main content search this site the leopold leadership program about fellows news fellowship information resources fellows login home change password all cohort reunion save the date june 19 21 2012 in this section 2012 newsletters newsletter archive new standards for sustainable shellfish farming sandra shumway published on october 20 2009 shumway standards for making shellfish farming sustainable have been released by the bivalve aquaculture dialogue of the world wildlife fund shellfish producers scientists and conservationists are among the stakeholders who took part sandy shumway 2001 a member of the global steering committee for the dialogue says the standards will help shell fishers to maintain their culture facilities in a sustainable manner while allowing shellfish aquaculture to continue to grow and help meet the global demand for more seafood click here to read and comment on the standards tags aquaculture fisheries sustainability 2011 leopold leadership program woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
